      • decodeStatement

        public static DestructorNode decodeStatement(TreeNode parent,
                             java.lang.String statement,
                             Location location)
        Decode the given statement into a DestructorNode instance, if possible. If it is not possible, this method returns null. A destructor must have the same name as the class that it is within preceded by a tilde (A tilde is a '~' located above the tab key). Destructors also do not have a return value and are always private. They never accept parameters, because they are never called programmatically.

        The only acceptable syntax input includes: "private ~ClassName()"
        Parameters:
        parent - The parent node of the statement.
        statement - The statement to try to decode into a DestructorNode instance.
        location - The location of the statement in the source code.
        Returns:
        The generated node, if it was possible to translated it into a DestructorNode.
